body:
I was going to suggest that we add some configurable polling logic possibly in [here](https://github.com/trufflesuite/truffle/blob/develop/packages/migrate/index.js#L189-L193), but it looks like we may already have this as either a [poorly documented or mostly undocumented feature](https://www.trufflesuite.com/docs/truffle/reference/configuration#networks) (see the bullet point about `websockets` & `confirmations` in a truffle config).

According to those above docs, something like the below should work and might resolve this issue ðŸ¤ž :

```javascript
module.exports = {
  ropsten: {
    network_id: "3",
    gas: 4000000,
    websockets: true, // (default: false)
    confirmations: 2, // (default: 0)
    provider: () => {
      return new HDWalletProvider(
        testnet.mneumonic,
        "https://ropsten.infura.io/v3/" + testnet.infura_id
      );
    }
  }
};
```

Side note: I've found [evidence](https://github.com/trufflesuite/truffle/issues/1680#issuecomment-506084223) that `websockets: true` does not need to be specified.

There is also possibly [another solution](https://ethereum.stackexchange.com/a/50038/51491) that might be something we could add to `@truffle/hdwallet-provider` (assuming this solution is actually related to this issue).

Please let us know if any of the above helps resolve this!
